Preheat the oven to 150C/300F/Gas 3 (130C fan).Heat two tablespoons of oil in a large frying pan. Add the lamb and fry in two batches until browned. Remove from the pan with a slotted spoon and set aside.Add the remaining oil to the pan. Add the onion and fry for 4-5 minutes, or until beginning to soften.Meanwhile, place the ginger, garlic and chilli into a small food processor and blend until finely chopped.Bash the cardamom pods with the end of a rolling pin to split the husks, then remove the seeds and grind them to a fine powder in a pestle and mortar. Add to the pan with the remaining spices and the garlic and ginger mixture.Add the remaining ingredients to the pan and add the lamb. Bring to the boil, then cover and place in the oven to simmer for 1Â½-2 hours, or until tender. Check the seasoning and serve with boiled rice.